  "texts": [
    "listed the problems of technology usage by older adults and specified the need for further studies to develop evidence-based techniques for cognitive impairment [37].",
    "In the recent years, in line with WHO definition [38], the assistive technologies for older adults gained new classification perspective besides technical approachpotential outcomes of the technologies which was expressed by Rolfe et al. [39].",
    "In this study, each technology was classified according to having different outcomes like social connectedness, autonomy and independence, mental health and wellbeing, physical health and safety.",
    "Although some technologies may have impact on more than one outcome, this categorization can be used as a starting point for older adults to examine technology options.",
    "Social connectedness is based on communication with family and friends by using text, video or video via laptops, mobile phones, or PCs."
  ]
}